  <slide>
    <title>Which disabilities benefit from SC 2.4.1 Bypass Blocks?</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li>Keyboard only users: People with physical impairments that limit use of the mouse or users of alternative input devices.</li>
        <li>Screen reader users: Originally the primary population but with improvements in web design and assistive technologies less important.  For example <code>h1</code> elements and/or <code>main</code> landmarks are typically used for the main content and screen have built-in commands to navigate to these locations.</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

